Bromus marginatus

    Authority   Nees ex Steudel
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3922

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A deep rooted, stout, erect, leafy grass. USES Used
   as a pasture grass often grown in mixture with alfalfa and sweet
   clover. GROWING PERIOD Short-lived perennial. COMMON NAMES Mountain
   bromegrass. FURTHER INF Mountain bromegrass is commonly found in
   canyons, meadows, and waste grounds of the northsestern United States
   and Mexico at elevations between 2100-2900 m.

   Sources
   SOURCES (B. marginatus Nees.)
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 167 [USE, DRA, FER]
   Duke J 1979 pp 94 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Heath M 1985 pp 205 [DEP, USE]

